This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on February 5, 2018. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities under Section 1238 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2018 to the Secretary of Defense, in coordination with the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Treasury, and the Director of National Intelligence. The President's authority to make such delegation is vested in him by the Constitution and the laws of the United States. The Secretary of Defense is also authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.